    "notes": "Detection focus: (1) PowerShell -Enc or -EncodedCommand spawned from a non-standard parent in AppData (not svchost/services/explorer). (2) Short-lived PowerShell writing .ps1 or .tmp files to AppData\\Local\\Temp followed immediately by a second PowerShell execution of that file. Key differentiators from benign: parent process path in AppData\\Roaming vs. System32, and the decode-drop-execute chain within a 3-second window. The benign Base64 PowerShell launches from svchost in System32 — a trusted, expected parent."
